cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with predicting failures of Head/Neck coils used in Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) by training a statistical model on sequential data collected over time. The use of image features and their variation over time to predict coil damage suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of statistical models and sequential data also suggests that the paper could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the use of MRI technology suggests that the paper could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
